rosaparaphrasen erfolgt, den bis ins 19. Jahrhundert nachgedruckten "Aesopus" von 1476/77, in dem diese stehen, zu einem der größten Bestseller der Buchgeschichte machten.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Okt 2018) 4aAesop. 4aFabel. 4aFables. 4aPhaedrus.1 aHolzberg, Niklas, eeditor.1 aSeibold, Stephanie.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2018z9783110603095oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311056232340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110576429423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110576429.jpg  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017